        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 16 at 1:38PM EDT by NWS Charleston WV</headline>
        <description>At 138 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a cluster of strong
thunderstorms along a line extending from 8 miles southwest of North
Bend State Park to 10 miles southeast of Harrisville. Movement was
northeast at 35 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Clarksburg, Harrisville, Stonewood, Nutter Fort, Salem, Pennsboro,
West Union, Anmoore, North Bend State Park, West Milford, Ellenboro,
Cairo, Pullman, Auburn, Wolf Summit, Pike, Berea, Highland,
Greenwood, and Blandville.

This includes the following highways...
Interstate 79 near mile marker 118.
Route 50 in West Virginia between mile markers 27 and 73.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
